    <label>GLBA Opt-Out Management</label>
    <protected>false</protected>
    <values>
        <field>Framework__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">GLBA</value>
    </values>
    <values>
        <field>Policy_Description__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">GLBA Privacy Rule requires financial institutions to provide customers with the right to opt-out of information sharing with nonaffiliated third parties. Organizations must process opt-out requests promptly and maintain records of opt-out status.</value>
    </values>
    <values>
        <field>Legal_Citation__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">GLBA Privacy Rule 16 CFR Part 313.7 - Form and method of providing opt-out notice</value>
    </values>
    <values>
        <field>Remediation_Steps__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">1. Implement opt-out request processing workflow.
2. Track opt-out status in customer records.
3. Process opt-out requests within 30 days of receipt.
4. Maintain audit trail of all opt-out requests and status changes.
5. Train staff on GLBA opt-out procedures and requirements.</value>
    </values>
